    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Because meetings really should only be for making decisions and clarifying actions (not having discussions).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Problem is, many organizations can’t tell the difference.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Hence, the three minute rule: If it’s going to take you longer than 3 minutes to decide on a solution, it’s a discussion, not a decision.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "A discussion is a conversation with two people (not whole departments) in order to reach a decision. Discussions take as long as it need to…but preferably over lunch.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Efficient meetings, on the other hand, make decisions and conclude with uncomplicated action steps for implementation.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Put it on the board and commence.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Quick decisions and concrete action steps. That's it. No hour long talks around the water cooler.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}